That issue - the output to stdout - is now fixed, and will be in the next release (~end of the month).

@devoncarew Thanks, but have you fixed only the output to stdout, or have you fixed the Flutter Inspector crash that is generating said output? When this output appears is when the inspector stops working. And my problem is the crash itself, not the output.

Also, where can I see the inspector's error logs?

It's likely that the output to stdout and the inspector no longer working were related - half on an inspector request likely got cut off.

You can view the intellij logs via `Help > Show logs`; the inspector view just writes issues there, as with the rest of the flutter plugin.
I searched the logs for the word "inspector" and couldn't find anything there.

Finally, I got the error in a small project. You can run it yourself if you need: https://github.com/marcglasberg/indexed_list_view/blob/master/example/lib/main_page_storage_key.dart
